1
00:01:04,682 --> 00:01:08,978
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

2
00:01:14,061 --> 00:01:15,896
9 YEARS AGO

3
00:01:15,980 --> 00:01:17,815
HR PERSONNEL ONLY

4
00:01:17,898 --> 00:01:20,025
2017 RESTRUCTURING TARGET LIST

5
00:01:23,487 --> 00:01:24,488
You're here.

6
00:01:29,868 --> 00:01:32,162
Good work, Mr. Gi.

7
00:01:32,538 --> 00:01:34,456
Why don't we grab a drink after?

8
00:01:34,915 --> 00:01:37,418
We can't do that yet.
We must seal the restructuring list.

9
00:01:37,793 --> 00:01:38,794
Hey.

10
00:01:38,877 --> 00:01:41,005
It doesn't matter who you fire.
It's all the same.

11
00:01:41,088 --> 00:01:42,298
We already selected a group

12
00:01:42,756 --> 00:01:44,300
and the vice president approved it.

13
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,635
Just make up your mind
and decide on half.

14
00:01:46,719 --> 00:01:47,720
Okay?

15
00:01:49,597 --> 00:01:51,849
<i>Su-jong, am I included</i>
<i>in the upcoming restructuring?</i>

16
00:01:56,645 --> 00:01:58,772
ASSISTANT MANAGER, SUNG JIN-YONG

17
00:02:07,615 --> 00:02:08,616
Here.

18
00:02:11,243 --> 00:02:12,828
Exactly a decade ago

19
00:02:12,911 --> 00:02:14,496
I was doing
what you're doing right now.

20
00:02:14,747 --> 00:02:17,291
It's a trick my superior taught me.

21
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:19,251
What's this?

22
00:02:21,003 --> 00:02:22,212
A coin flip.

23
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,757
We're restructuring
by flipping a coin?

24
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:27,092
Hey, what's so bad
about doing a coin flip?

25
00:02:27,551 --> 00:02:29,261
Nothing is fairer than that.

26
00:02:29,511 --> 00:02:31,472
It doesn't have
any prejudices or emotions.

27
00:02:31,930 --> 00:02:33,891
No school ties or regionalism.

28
00:02:34,183 --> 00:02:36,185
Front or back? Yes or no?

29
00:02:37,436 --> 00:02:38,771
That's all there is.

30
00:02:39,396 --> 00:02:40,397
Okay?

31
00:02:41,649 --> 00:02:42,733
You also need a promotion.

32
00:02:44,401 --> 00:02:45,402
Wrap it up.

33
00:02:45,944 --> 00:02:47,571
Don't take it seriously.

34
00:02:51,784 --> 00:02:52,785
Goodness.

35
00:03:03,796 --> 00:03:05,422
Seon, what did the kid's mom say?

36
00:03:07,007 --> 00:03:08,133
Da-rae.

37
00:03:08,217 --> 00:03:10,219
You're doing a great job.
Keep it going.

38
00:03:12,554 --> 00:03:13,764
Well

39
00:03:13,847 --> 00:03:15,808
I heard Da-rae ignored the kid first.

40
00:03:16,225 --> 00:03:18,018
But it doesn't make any sense.

41
00:03:18,644 --> 00:03:21,397
You're right. She wouldn't do that.

42
00:03:21,772 --> 00:03:23,857
They're clearly leaving her out.

43
00:03:23,941 --> 00:03:26,193
- How many times has this happened?
- You're right.

44
00:03:26,902 --> 00:03:28,028
We should let her study abroad.

45
00:03:29,196 --> 00:03:30,197
Study abroad?

46
00:03:31,031 --> 00:03:33,158
You know Da-rae is gifted.

47
00:03:33,242 --> 00:03:34,743
The states have a good system

48
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,870
and Da-rae will love it there, too.

49
00:03:36,954 --> 00:03:38,580
Yes, of course she'll love it.

50
00:03:38,664 --> 00:03:39,832
But we can't afford it.

51
00:03:40,666 --> 00:03:42,000
We should find a way.

52
00:03:42,501 --> 00:03:44,878
Things are tough at work these days.

53
00:03:44,962 --> 00:03:46,171
Do you remember Jin-yong?

54
00:03:46,797 --> 00:03:49,133
He's on the restructuring list

55
00:03:49,216 --> 00:03:50,718
and I don't know if I'll make it.

56
00:03:52,219 --> 00:03:55,055
Just do as your company says
and stick around no matter what.

57
00:03:55,431 --> 00:03:57,266
I'm not a slave.

58
00:03:57,725 --> 00:04:01,395
I should find a business item
and start my own thing.

59
00:04:01,687 --> 00:04:02,688
Su-jong.

60
00:04:03,021 --> 00:04:04,815
We are slaves.

61
00:04:04,898 --> 00:04:06,608
We have another 20 years
until we're freed.

62
00:04:09,653 --> 00:04:11,280
Life was never easy for us.

63
00:04:11,613 --> 00:04:13,824
Let's think of Da-rae and hold on.

64
00:04:14,450 --> 00:04:16,785
I'll see if graveyard shifts are
available in emergency rooms.

65
00:04:18,746 --> 00:04:19,747
Okay.

66
00:04:24,293 --> 00:04:26,837
We need 125,679,200 won more...

67
00:04:32,259 --> 00:04:33,761
<i>What will happen to me?</i>

68
00:04:37,681 --> 00:04:39,475
ASSISTANT MANAGER, SUNG JIN-YONG

69
00:04:43,562 --> 00:04:46,690
Drop or pass?

70
00:04:48,066 --> 00:04:49,067
Pass.

71
00:04:53,989 --> 00:04:54,990
No.

72
00:04:57,367 --> 00:04:58,368
Dang it.

73
00:04:58,702 --> 00:04:59,703
What are you up to?

74
00:05:02,372 --> 00:05:03,457
What's this coin?

75
00:05:03,957 --> 00:05:05,834
What? Hey.

76
00:05:07,127 --> 00:05:08,462
Why are you ignoring my message?

77
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,089
You messaged me?

78
00:05:13,550 --> 00:05:15,511
You know I got scammed
by my landlord.

79
00:05:15,844 --> 00:05:18,430
My kid is three now,
and we might end up on the streets.

80
00:05:18,931 --> 00:05:20,432
I really can't go this time.

81
00:05:21,308 --> 00:05:23,310
Yes, right. Of course.

82
00:05:24,269 --> 00:05:25,354
Do you want to go for dinner?

83
00:05:25,938 --> 00:05:27,523
Sorry, I have to meet someone.

84
00:05:27,898 --> 00:05:29,024
Are you avoiding me?

85
00:05:29,107 --> 00:05:30,943
What are you talking about?

86
00:05:32,569 --> 00:05:33,570
See?

87
00:05:33,654 --> 00:05:34,988
HWAL-SUNG
I'M HERE, LET'S EAT

88
00:05:35,906 --> 00:05:36,907
Okay.

89
00:05:38,617 --> 00:05:40,953
- Let's grab a drink sometime soon.
- Sure.

90
00:05:41,995 --> 00:05:42,996
Don't work too hard.

91
00:05:43,789 --> 00:05:44,790
I won't.

92
00:06:06,645 --> 00:06:08,355
Hey, why are you stuck in a corner?

93
00:06:09,439 --> 00:06:11,400
I told you not to order
the noodles ahead of time.

94
00:06:11,483 --> 00:06:13,735
- It'll get soggy.
- It just came out.

95
00:06:14,278 --> 00:06:16,363
Come on, man.

96
00:06:16,989 --> 00:06:17,990
Drink first, noodles later?

97
00:06:18,532 --> 00:06:19,533
No.

98
00:06:19,616 --> 00:06:21,118
I'll accept but not drink.

99
00:06:21,201 --> 00:06:22,536
I have an early start tomorrow.

100
00:06:24,288 --> 00:06:27,416
Yi-gyeong wants me to take
the civil servant exam.

101
00:06:27,499 --> 00:06:29,710
I've never studied in my life,
so how am I going to do that now?

102
00:06:29,793 --> 00:06:32,129
Forget it. You'd be more of a patriot
doing something else.

103
00:06:32,212 --> 00:06:33,297
I agree.

104
00:06:33,672 --> 00:06:35,674
For my country's sake,
I won't become a civil servant.

105
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:38,260
Why did you want to see me
all of a sudden?

106
00:06:39,428 --> 00:06:40,429
Friend.

107
00:06:42,055 --> 00:06:43,265
Do you want to be a landlord?

108
00:06:46,184 --> 00:06:47,185
What?

109
00:06:48,395 --> 00:06:49,396
What do you think?

110
00:06:50,397 --> 00:06:51,565
What do I know?

111
00:06:51,648 --> 00:06:54,067
- Isn't this building a bit too old?
- Hey.

112
00:06:54,151 --> 00:06:56,403
It's about the location,
not the building.

113
00:06:56,486 --> 00:06:59,031
Real estate is all about location.

114
00:06:59,323 --> 00:07:00,657
What about the location?

115
00:07:01,825 --> 00:07:03,911
This is top-class information.

116
00:07:04,453 --> 00:07:05,704
It's for your ears only.

117
00:07:06,246 --> 00:07:07,998
You're doing this again.

118
00:07:08,332 --> 00:07:09,333
Hey.

119
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:13,211
This entire area
is up for redevelopment.

120
00:07:13,295 --> 00:07:14,296
Redevelopment?

121
00:07:15,923 --> 00:07:18,842
Yes, right here, the prime location
in the middle of Seoul.

122
00:07:20,552 --> 00:07:22,763
Why are you sharing this with me?

123
00:07:22,846 --> 00:07:25,182
Everyone says I should hard pass
when someone says that.

124
00:07:26,058 --> 00:07:27,476
We aren't strangers.

125
00:07:28,352 --> 00:07:30,020
It's because I can't afford it alone.

126
00:07:30,479 --> 00:07:32,189
Let's invest in it together.

127
00:07:32,272 --> 00:07:33,732
DARAE HAIR SALON

128
00:07:36,735 --> 00:07:39,071
DARAE HAIR SALON

129
00:07:40,781 --> 00:07:41,782
Hey.

130
00:07:41,865 --> 00:07:43,158
We'll go exactly 50-50.

131
00:07:43,241 --> 00:07:44,743
You put in 1.2 billion,
I put in 1.2 billion.

132
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:48,121
But I need you to pay 200 million
as the down payment.

133
00:07:48,205 --> 00:07:50,958
You can cover the interest
with the monthly rent.

134
00:07:51,458 --> 00:07:53,377
Let's hang around
until it gets redeveloped.

135
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:55,170
I don't have 1.2 billion won.

136
00:07:55,420 --> 00:07:56,672
You can take out a loan.

137
00:07:57,130 --> 00:07:59,341
You can get up to 80%
when you buy a building.

138
00:07:59,758 --> 00:08:01,677
How are you going to pay for it?

139
00:08:02,970 --> 00:08:05,806
I am the son-in-law
of Madam Jeon Yang-ja.

140
00:08:07,015 --> 00:08:08,475
I hadn't been

141
00:08:08,558 --> 00:08:11,311
in her good books until now,
and I knew I wasn't welcome.

142
00:08:11,395 --> 00:08:14,189
But things seemed to have changed

143
00:08:14,272 --> 00:08:16,233
after Yi-gyeong got pregnant.

144
00:08:20,487 --> 00:08:22,823
Why should I pay the down payment?
What about you?

145
00:08:23,824 --> 00:08:25,659
I don't have the cash flow
at the moment.

146
00:08:26,785 --> 00:08:28,620
But let's have the deed
under your name.

147
00:08:29,204 --> 00:08:30,372
Do you trust me?

148
00:08:30,455 --> 00:08:31,456
I don't.

149
00:08:32,165 --> 00:08:33,917
I'm always two moves ahead of you.

150
00:08:34,584 --> 00:08:36,837
When you feel like stabbing my back,
take a look at yours.

151
00:08:38,005 --> 00:08:39,006
Jeez.

152
00:08:49,891 --> 00:08:52,019
BADUK CLUBHOUSE

153
00:08:52,102 --> 00:08:53,645
STUDYING ABROAD: WHY U.S.A

154
00:08:53,729 --> 00:08:55,272
EXPENSES FOR STUDYING ABROAD

155
00:08:55,355 --> 00:08:57,149
IT DEPENDS ON THE TYPE OF SCHOOL,
AREA, AND RESIDENCE...

156
00:08:57,607 --> 00:08:59,192
300 MILLION TO 500 MILLION
180 MILLION TO 300 MILLION

157
00:09:01,069 --> 00:09:02,821
Should we live as landlords?

158
00:09:05,365 --> 00:09:07,784
What's going on with you this time?

159
00:09:13,665 --> 00:09:14,666
Are you serious?

160
00:09:15,709 --> 00:09:16,918
You said we should try.

161
00:09:17,627 --> 00:09:18,837
I didn't say that.

162
00:09:19,087 --> 00:09:21,298
I said we should make honest money
without pulling too many tricks.

163
00:09:21,673 --> 00:09:23,091
What do you mean by honest money?

164
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:25,719
Da-rae isn't like us.

165
00:09:25,802 --> 00:09:26,928
We must bring her up differently.

166
00:09:28,472 --> 00:09:29,598
Here's the thing.

167
00:09:30,015 --> 00:09:31,141
It was Hwal-sung's offer

168
00:09:31,224 --> 00:09:32,851
and we just need to make
the down payment.

169
00:09:33,143 --> 00:09:35,270
He's quick with these things,
you know.

170
00:09:35,353 --> 00:09:36,855
And he has a wealthy mother-in-law.

171
00:09:37,481 --> 00:09:38,732
What about work?

172
00:09:38,815 --> 00:09:40,025
I should keep working.

173
00:09:40,108 --> 00:09:42,235
Hwal-sung will manage the building.

174
00:09:43,487 --> 00:09:44,780
Da-rae's parents?

175
00:09:44,863 --> 00:09:46,114
- Yes.
- Yes.

176
00:09:46,198 --> 00:09:47,240
Let's go.

177
00:09:52,871 --> 00:09:55,499
Why am I craving sweets like a kid
after quitting smoking?

178
00:09:55,582 --> 00:09:58,001
I can't believe Da-rae made me quit.

179
00:09:58,668 --> 00:10:00,295
You're such a family man.

180
00:10:00,629 --> 00:10:02,339
Seon told me already.
Is 200 million enough?

181
00:10:02,589 --> 00:10:05,008
Yes, I got the loan approval
from the bank

182
00:10:05,092 --> 00:10:06,802
so with 200 million, it's done.

183
00:10:06,885 --> 00:10:07,928
A happy ending.

184
00:10:08,011 --> 00:10:09,012
Okay.

185
00:10:10,138 --> 00:10:11,473
Let's do this.

186
00:10:12,641 --> 00:10:13,642
You got it.

187
00:10:15,227 --> 00:10:16,353
Thank you so much.

188
00:10:16,436 --> 00:10:18,146
I'll pay you back immediately
with the interest.

189
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:19,689
Stop it. I don't need that.

190
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:21,191
I don't have any use for money.

191
00:10:22,192 --> 00:10:23,401
You don't owe me any interest.

192
00:10:24,653 --> 00:10:27,614
I seriously do not think
you are ordinary in any way.

193
00:10:28,073 --> 00:10:30,283
You're the human embodiment
of the word nice.

194
00:10:31,201 --> 00:10:32,953
I told you that you'd make it big.

195
00:10:33,203 --> 00:10:35,831
Does this mean my sister
is now the wife of a landlord?

196
00:10:35,914 --> 00:10:36,915
Yes.

197
00:10:37,499 --> 00:10:38,834
And it's all thanks to you.

198
00:10:39,626 --> 00:10:41,128
It's because
you live a diligent life.

199
00:10:43,588 --> 00:10:44,923
Thank you so much.

200
00:10:45,590 --> 00:10:47,467
HR PERSONNEL ONLY

201
00:10:47,843 --> 00:10:48,844
Jeez.

202
00:10:52,347 --> 00:10:53,348
Yes?

203
00:10:54,141 --> 00:10:55,142
Are you done?

204
00:10:55,225 --> 00:10:56,226
No, not yet.

205
00:10:58,186 --> 00:10:59,187
Let me see that.

206
00:11:08,989 --> 00:11:11,700
ASSISTANT MANAGER, SUNG JIN-YONG: ?

207
00:11:12,284 --> 00:11:13,577
Hey, what about Jin-yong?

208
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:14,870
Sir, you know what?

209
00:11:14,953 --> 00:11:16,830
Jin-yong is in a bit of a situation.

210
00:11:17,789 --> 00:11:19,624
Situation, my foot.

211
00:11:19,708 --> 00:11:21,376
No one here is in a good situation.

212
00:11:21,835 --> 00:11:22,836
Right?

213
00:11:23,170 --> 00:11:24,671
If people think you favor your friend

214
00:11:24,754 --> 00:11:26,464
it'll cause problems later.

215
00:11:27,132 --> 00:11:29,467
The closer they are to you,
the more impartial you must be.

216
00:11:30,427 --> 00:11:31,428
Okay?

217
00:11:31,845 --> 00:11:32,846
Yes, sir.

218
00:11:33,930 --> 00:11:36,266
That's the only way HR gets adorned.

219
00:11:36,766 --> 00:11:38,101
Yu-chan's struggling too, isn't he?

220
00:11:38,185 --> 00:11:40,020
Look at how the sunlight
hits the place.

221
00:11:40,437 --> 00:11:41,521
Look at this.

222
00:11:41,605 --> 00:11:43,815
The previous landlord was an engineer

223
00:11:43,899 --> 00:11:45,901
so he fixed up everything neatly
while he owned it.

224
00:11:45,984 --> 00:11:47,235
I mean, look.

225
00:11:47,319 --> 00:11:50,739
The place is really old,
but nothing here is broken.

226
00:11:51,990 --> 00:11:53,533
Is the landlord not here?

227
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:54,951
He got locked up

228
00:11:55,035 --> 00:11:57,037
- after gambling at an illegal den.
- Really?

229
00:11:57,370 --> 00:11:58,580
Take a look inside.

230
00:12:01,166 --> 00:12:02,167
It looks clean.

231
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,668
It does, doesn't it?

232
00:12:04,002 --> 00:12:05,253
Consider yourselves lucky.

233
00:12:05,337 --> 00:12:08,423
You couldn't have found this
at this price without that incident.

234
00:12:08,506 --> 00:12:09,549
Right.

235
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:13,803
You must pay the balance
within a week to get the low price.

236
00:12:14,179 --> 00:12:16,264
- Did you tell him?
- Yes, don't worry about it.

237
00:12:16,723 --> 00:12:18,850
Okay. Now, over here.

238
00:12:20,894 --> 00:12:22,354
Is this a storage?

239
00:12:22,437 --> 00:12:24,147
It's huge on the inside.

240
00:12:24,231 --> 00:12:25,357
You can walk in and look.

241
00:12:26,107 --> 00:12:30,362
This was made for the tenants

242
00:12:31,071 --> 00:12:32,906
but I'm not sure if it's in use.

243
00:12:33,198 --> 00:12:35,116
- It's a cold storage.
- Yes.

244
00:12:36,868 --> 00:12:37,953
It's huge.

245
00:12:38,036 --> 00:12:39,454
It's spacious and nice.

246
00:12:39,537 --> 00:12:40,538
So?

247
00:12:40,914 --> 00:12:42,540
Are you going to take it?

248
00:12:49,297 --> 00:12:51,174
SEJEONG YEONGGWANG REALTOR

249
00:12:51,466 --> 00:12:53,885
Now, read through the contract.

250
00:12:53,969 --> 00:12:54,970
Here you go.

251
00:12:55,053 --> 00:12:56,179
Your seal right here.

252
00:12:56,846 --> 00:12:58,348
- Have some tea.
- Okay.

253
00:13:03,687 --> 00:13:06,481
SELLER: KIM YEONG-HWA, LEE GYU-HAK
BUYER: GI SU-JONG

254
00:13:09,025 --> 00:13:10,527
-Right here?
- Yes.

255
00:13:12,237 --> 00:13:13,363
And send the down payment

256
00:13:13,655 --> 00:13:15,115
- Yes.
- to this bank account.

257
00:13:18,952 --> 00:13:22,539
TO KIM YEONG-HWA
JANGSEOP BANK

258
00:13:22,622 --> 00:13:24,249
200,000,000 WON

259
00:13:24,874 --> 00:13:26,960
- The transfer went through.
- Okay.

260
00:13:27,961 --> 00:13:29,254
- Please give me a moment.
- Sure.

261
00:13:29,337 --> 00:13:30,839
- I'll write you a receipt.
- Okay.

262
00:13:34,259 --> 00:13:35,343
Hello, Mr. Landlord.

263
00:13:35,593 --> 00:13:36,636
You psycho.

264
00:13:38,763 --> 00:13:39,764
Hey.

265
00:13:40,223 --> 00:13:41,391
Should we hit up that place?

266
00:13:41,474 --> 00:13:42,475
Where?

267
00:13:44,644 --> 00:13:45,854
I can't believe this.

268
00:13:45,937 --> 00:13:47,355
How did I live to see this day?

269
00:13:47,439 --> 00:13:48,857
Oh, goodness.

270
00:13:50,191 --> 00:13:53,403
Yes, we were nothing but bums.

271
00:13:53,486 --> 00:13:56,197
Who would've imagined
that we'd become landlords?

272
00:13:56,281 --> 00:13:57,365
Tell me about it.

273
00:14:01,786 --> 00:14:04,706
When my father passed away

274
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:07,250
both my mom and I were at a loss.

275
00:14:07,334 --> 00:14:09,711
But you lent me a million won.

276
00:14:09,961 --> 00:14:11,338
I can never forget that.

277
00:14:11,588 --> 00:14:13,965
Yes, you see?
You can't do anything without me.

278
00:14:16,801 --> 00:14:20,013
Yes, I'll give you a little credit.

279
00:14:20,096 --> 00:14:21,097
Anyway

280
00:14:21,181 --> 00:14:24,059
how did a high school kid like you
come up with a million won?

281
00:14:24,142 --> 00:14:26,770
- I've always been dying to know.
- I remember the good old days.

282
00:14:27,312 --> 00:14:29,064
I asked my dad for help.

283
00:14:29,314 --> 00:14:30,815
I said you were having a tough time

284
00:14:30,899 --> 00:14:32,400
and asked if he could help.

285
00:14:32,776 --> 00:14:34,903
I'm so grateful for him.

286
00:14:34,986 --> 00:14:36,905
I should've thanked him for his help.

287
00:14:38,073 --> 00:14:39,741
Let me make a belated confession.

288
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:42,619
He gave me two million won.

289
00:14:43,995 --> 00:14:45,413
I took a million.

290
00:14:46,247 --> 00:14:47,540
Look at this punk.

291
00:14:49,042 --> 00:14:50,668
You remember, right?

292
00:14:50,752 --> 00:14:52,837
I was dating Hye-jin,
the queen of Eunyeong Girls' High.

293
00:14:53,088 --> 00:14:54,506
It cost me a fortune

294
00:14:55,465 --> 00:14:56,591
to date that girl.

295
00:14:57,092 --> 00:14:58,093
Gosh.

296
00:14:59,677 --> 00:15:01,679
You haven't received
the rest of the balance?

297
00:15:01,763 --> 00:15:03,890
<i>The bank sent their portion</i>

298
00:15:04,265 --> 00:15:05,809
<i>but not the rest that you owe.</i>

299
00:15:06,142 --> 00:15:07,394
There must be a misunderstanding.

300
00:15:07,477 --> 00:15:09,145
I talked with him yesterday.

301
00:15:09,229 --> 00:15:10,688
My friend said
he'd send it over right away.

302
00:15:10,939 --> 00:15:12,565
This isn't a joke.

303
00:15:12,899 --> 00:15:14,734
You must make the payment
on the promised date.

304
00:15:14,818 --> 00:15:18,988
I talked to the previous owner
and said you'd send it within the day

305
00:15:19,072 --> 00:15:20,365
<i>so can you do that right away?</i>

306
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:23,243
Well, sir, if the deal falls through

307
00:15:23,326 --> 00:15:24,786
can I get the down payment back?

308
00:15:25,453 --> 00:15:26,579
No.

309
00:15:27,122 --> 00:15:28,415
Don't you know
what a down payment is?

310
00:15:30,125 --> 00:15:31,126
Well, right.

311
00:15:31,918 --> 00:15:33,086
In that case

312
00:15:33,169 --> 00:15:35,338
can you give me a few more days?

313
00:15:35,422 --> 00:15:37,215
I'll double your commission.

314
00:15:37,590 --> 00:15:40,927
Can you talk to the seller for me?

315
00:15:41,928 --> 00:15:43,388
<i>Fine, but double the commission.</i>

316
00:15:43,471 --> 00:15:44,722
Yes, please do that for me.

317
00:15:45,140 --> 00:15:46,516
Darn it.

318
00:15:48,184 --> 00:15:50,311
HWAL-SUNG

319
00:15:50,395 --> 00:15:51,604
Man.

320
00:15:54,566 --> 00:15:55,859
ASSISTANT MANAGER, SUNG JIN-YONG

321
00:15:58,194 --> 00:16:00,029
Hey, what do you think you're doing?

322
00:16:00,488 --> 00:16:01,739
What are you looking at?

323
00:16:05,702 --> 00:16:07,328
You asshole!

324
00:16:26,431 --> 00:16:27,432
What's up with you?

325
00:16:27,515 --> 00:16:28,516
What do you mean?

326
00:16:28,975 --> 00:16:30,727
What happened
to the remaining balance?

327
00:16:35,148 --> 00:16:36,441
I'm sorry, man.

328
00:16:36,524 --> 00:16:37,734
I don't think I can help.

329
00:16:38,735 --> 00:16:39,861
What about my money?

330
00:16:39,944 --> 00:16:40,945
What money?

331
00:16:41,029 --> 00:16:42,280
The down payment.

332
00:16:45,283 --> 00:16:47,327
Just consider it a good life lesson.

333
00:16:47,702 --> 00:16:50,205
Are you out of your mind?
I borrowed it from my brother-in-law.

334
00:16:50,538 --> 00:16:51,539
Su-jong.

335
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:55,043
I'm in a situation, too.

336
00:16:55,919 --> 00:16:58,421
And money is something
that comes and goes

337
00:16:58,671 --> 00:17:00,340
and ebbs and flows in life, right?

338
00:17:00,423 --> 00:17:02,675
What kind of nonsense
are you blabbing about?

339
00:17:03,468 --> 00:17:05,094
Stop talking crap

340
00:17:05,178 --> 00:17:06,304
and call your wife now.

341
00:17:06,387 --> 00:17:08,223
- No, ask your mother-in-law.
- Hey!

342
00:17:09,516 --> 00:17:12,018
Don't mess with my family, you punk.

343
00:17:12,101 --> 00:17:13,269
What did you say?

344
00:17:14,687 --> 00:17:15,855
Is that all you can say right now?

345
00:17:17,023 --> 00:17:18,233
Fine, let go.

346
00:17:20,026 --> 00:17:21,152
I'll talk to them.

347
00:17:27,158 --> 00:17:28,159
Gosh.

348
00:17:34,624 --> 00:17:36,459
Is this all our friendship is worth
after 30 years?

349
00:17:44,551 --> 00:17:47,053
GYUN, 200 MILLION WON

350
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,435
Mr. Kim.

351
00:17:54,519 --> 00:17:58,606
MACHINE ENGINEER MR. KIM

352
00:17:58,690 --> 00:17:59,774
Mr. Kim.

353
00:18:08,324 --> 00:18:10,076
Hello, Mr. Kim.

354
00:18:10,159 --> 00:18:11,828
It's Gi Su-jong
of Yongshin Trading calling.

355
00:18:13,496 --> 00:18:14,706
Well...

356
00:18:14,789 --> 00:18:17,208
I'm not calling because of business.

357
00:18:18,585 --> 00:18:21,129
Is there a way
I can take out some more loans?

358
00:18:21,546 --> 00:18:23,923
NARA BANK
LOAN PRODUCTS

359
00:18:24,007 --> 00:18:26,259
It's listed as 2.4 billion won, so...

360
00:18:40,356 --> 00:18:41,941
What's wrong?
Do you have something to say?

361
00:18:46,195 --> 00:18:47,238
Should we move?

362
00:18:47,947 --> 00:18:48,948
Move?

363
00:18:49,574 --> 00:18:52,076
The thing is, I've run out of money.

364
00:18:53,286 --> 00:18:55,705
Wait, what is it? Is it serious?

365
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,045
I'm about to lose the down payment.

366
00:19:03,296 --> 00:19:04,589
That's Gyun's money, right?

367
00:19:10,011 --> 00:19:11,763
(Are you two fighting?)

368
00:19:13,556 --> 00:19:15,099
(You should talk it out.)

369
00:19:15,558 --> 00:19:17,769
All right. Don't worry.

370
00:19:20,897 --> 00:19:22,398
Seon.

371
00:19:23,358 --> 00:19:24,692
There's one more thing.

372
00:19:30,281 --> 00:19:31,407
I'm leaving.

373
00:19:31,491 --> 00:19:32,492
Yes, sir.

374
00:19:33,159 --> 00:19:34,827
The report is due tomorrow.
You know that, right?

375
00:19:35,411 --> 00:19:36,412
Yes, sir.

376
00:19:36,829 --> 00:19:38,456
Don't take it too seriously.

377
00:19:55,682 --> 00:19:58,101
That wasn't so hard, was it?
Why did you drag this out?

378
00:19:58,768 --> 00:20:00,103
Wasn't it easier than you thought?

379
00:20:03,064 --> 00:20:05,692
Jeong-min, Su-yeon, Min-seok.

380
00:20:05,775 --> 00:20:06,776
Su-jong...

381
00:20:08,236 --> 00:20:09,237
What is this?

382
00:20:11,406 --> 00:20:12,615
Jin-yong is out

383
00:20:14,409 --> 00:20:15,535
and you're in.

384
00:20:15,785 --> 00:20:18,162
Yes, I made my decision.

385
00:20:19,872 --> 00:20:20,873
Why?

386
00:20:21,708 --> 00:20:22,834
Do you need a large sum of money?

387
00:20:26,838 --> 00:20:28,464
Was this the only way?

388
00:20:28,756 --> 00:20:29,841
Hey.

389
00:20:29,924 --> 00:20:31,426
The economy isn't good right now.

390
00:20:31,801 --> 00:20:33,219
You should keep your job.

391
00:20:33,845 --> 00:20:34,846
You have a kid, too.

392
00:20:36,013 --> 00:20:38,599
But you already know I'm expendable.

393
00:20:38,975 --> 00:20:41,894
I should find my own way to survive
before it's too late.

394
00:20:44,063 --> 00:20:45,064
Wait, are you doing this

395
00:20:46,315 --> 00:20:47,859
because you feel guilty?

396
00:20:48,443 --> 00:20:49,444
Hey.

397
00:20:50,153 --> 00:20:52,113
It hurts me too. It does. Okay?

398
00:20:52,447 --> 00:20:54,115
But this is our job. What can we do?

399
00:20:54,657 --> 00:20:55,742
Think it over.

400
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:57,243
No, sir.

401
00:20:59,454 --> 00:21:00,872
I'm going to take up another job.

402
00:21:01,998 --> 00:21:03,040
What?

403
00:21:04,709 --> 00:21:05,710
Leasing service.

404
00:21:07,670 --> 00:21:09,422
BUSINESS CLOSURE
DARAE HAIR SALON

405
00:21:11,132 --> 00:21:12,383
DARAE HAIR SALON

406
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:14,218
CLOSING DUE TO INTERNAL REASONS
THANK YOU FOR YOUR SUPPORT

407
00:21:19,015 --> 00:21:20,933
Hello, do you sell <i>sirutteok?</i>

408
00:21:21,017 --> 00:21:22,393
- Yes, over there.
- Okay.

409
00:21:30,234 --> 00:21:31,235
Excuse me.

410
00:21:32,695 --> 00:21:34,781
I'm the new landlord.

411
00:21:35,865 --> 00:21:36,991
Do you own this business?

412
00:21:37,742 --> 00:21:39,660
I brought some for you.

413
00:21:42,079 --> 00:21:43,498
When you got the place...

414
00:21:48,503 --> 00:21:50,630
you knew this area wasn't up
for redevelopment anymore, right?

415
00:21:51,547 --> 00:21:52,548
Sorry?

416
00:21:52,965 --> 00:21:54,217
It was a waste of effort.

417
00:21:57,762 --> 00:21:58,846
CHEONGAN DAILY

418
00:22:01,682 --> 00:22:03,184
SEJEONG-RO ZONE 3 UP FOR REASSESSMENT

419
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:04,685
DUE TO THE OPPOSITION
OF LOCAL MERCHANTS

420
00:22:08,940 --> 00:22:10,149
<i>Where are you?</i>

421
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:11,359
<i>We unloaded all our stuff.</i>

422
00:22:12,902 --> 00:22:13,903
Right.

423
00:22:31,212 --> 00:22:32,338
Hey, Min Hwal-sung.

424
00:22:32,630 --> 00:22:33,840
Hey, friend. You're here.

425
00:22:33,923 --> 00:22:36,634
Your place isn't half bad.

426
00:22:36,717 --> 00:22:37,718
Nice find.

427
00:22:39,262 --> 00:22:40,471
We need to talk.

428
00:22:41,097 --> 00:22:42,098
What?

429
00:22:42,932 --> 00:22:44,600
You knew the redevelopment
fell through, right?

430
00:22:44,684 --> 00:22:45,935
Was that why you backed out?

431
00:22:47,186 --> 00:22:48,729
Who told you that?

432
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:51,399
Man, this punk heard
a weird rumor out there.

433
00:22:51,482 --> 00:22:53,067
I'm not an idiot, okay?

434
00:22:53,317 --> 00:22:54,652
They said I got screwed over.

435
00:22:55,695 --> 00:22:56,863
Was it the old man on floor three?

436
00:22:59,198 --> 00:23:02,326
Redevelopments
don't happen overnight.

437
00:23:02,410 --> 00:23:05,621
It's something old people talk about
because they get bored.

438
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:08,916
This wasn't what you said
in the beginning!

439
00:23:09,375 --> 00:23:10,543
Why did you back out?

440
00:23:12,503 --> 00:23:14,714
Da-rae is watching you. Stop it.

441
00:23:15,882 --> 00:23:17,717
Redevelopment isn't easy.

442
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,052
Give it time.
The building isn't going anywhere.

443
00:23:20,845 --> 00:23:22,054
I'm sorry, man.

444
00:23:22,597 --> 00:23:25,600
I know it must be disconcerting

445
00:23:26,684 --> 00:23:28,644
but there was an accident
with my fund.

446
00:23:28,936 --> 00:23:30,771
What accident? Tell me.

447
00:23:30,855 --> 00:23:32,857
I'll explain it to you later.

448
00:23:33,441 --> 00:23:34,692
The redevelopment project

449
00:23:34,775 --> 00:23:37,570
will get going once again
when the government changes.

450
00:23:37,653 --> 00:23:39,071
That's two years max.

451
00:23:39,614 --> 00:23:41,115
Just hang in there, okay?

452
00:23:41,198 --> 00:23:42,408
Darn it.

453
00:23:42,825 --> 00:23:43,826
Hey.

454
00:23:44,660 --> 00:23:45,661
Hwal-sung.

455
00:23:45,745 --> 00:23:47,163
There's a playground down there.

456
00:23:47,246 --> 00:23:48,664
Can you babysit Da-rae for a moment?

457
00:23:48,748 --> 00:23:50,750
We'll tidy things up here quickly.

458
00:23:50,833 --> 00:23:52,585
- Let's get <i>jjajangmyeon </i>later.
- Should we?

459
00:23:52,668 --> 00:23:54,670
I think Yi-gyeong might show up.

460
00:23:54,754 --> 00:23:56,505
Really? That's great news.

461
00:23:57,381 --> 00:23:58,382
Da-rae.

462
00:23:59,342 --> 00:24:01,093
- All right!
- I'm going to get you.

463
00:24:02,970 --> 00:24:04,055
Are you having fun?

464
00:24:05,514 --> 00:24:07,350
Let's fly up!

465
00:24:07,433 --> 00:24:08,935
One second.

466
00:24:12,271 --> 00:24:13,272
Hey, Yi-gyeong.

467
00:24:15,566 --> 00:24:16,567
What?

468
00:24:17,318 --> 00:24:18,819
You should get some rest at home.

469
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:21,322
No, it'd be great if you came.

470
00:24:24,116 --> 00:24:25,451
Mrs. Jeon? Why?

471
00:24:27,703 --> 00:24:28,955
I have to call her?

472
00:24:31,749 --> 00:24:33,960
All right. Bye.

473
00:24:40,132 --> 00:24:41,133
Hello? Mrs. Jeon.

474
00:24:41,676 --> 00:24:43,427
I heard you wanted me to call you.

475
00:24:44,220 --> 00:24:47,848
Oh, that thing?
I already said that before I came.

476
00:24:49,892 --> 00:24:50,893
Really?

477
00:24:52,353 --> 00:24:55,272
In that case, I'll check again.

478
00:24:55,898 --> 00:24:57,900
I'll call you right away.

479
00:24:57,984 --> 00:25:00,319
Yes, I'll send it over right away.

480
00:25:09,078 --> 00:25:10,329
- Hwal-sung.
- Hey.

481
00:25:10,413 --> 00:25:11,497
- Where's Da-rae?
- You're here.

482
00:25:11,580 --> 00:25:12,581
What?

483
00:25:17,878 --> 00:25:19,714
Da-rae... She was right here.

484
00:25:20,881 --> 00:25:22,508
What? Da-rae...

485
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:24,552
What? What are you talking about?

486
00:25:25,594 --> 00:25:27,013
Wait, what?

487
00:25:27,930 --> 00:25:28,931
Where did she go?

488
00:25:29,974 --> 00:25:31,600
Darn it. I'll look for her.

489
00:25:32,852 --> 00:25:33,853
Oh, no.

490
00:25:35,146 --> 00:25:36,939
Go that way. I'll go this way.

491
00:25:37,857 --> 00:25:38,858
What? Darn it.

492
00:26:01,922 --> 00:26:02,923
She's not around, right?

493
00:26:03,549 --> 00:26:05,051
- I'll call Gyun.
- Okay.

494
00:26:08,012 --> 00:26:09,555
Su-jong, over there.

495
00:26:12,558 --> 00:26:13,559
Hey.

496
00:26:37,958 --> 00:26:43,422
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

497
00:26:44,173 --> 00:26:46,509
EPISODE 9

498
00:27:43,566 --> 00:27:45,734
SEON

499
00:27:55,870 --> 00:27:57,705
- Hey.
<i>- Where are you?</i>

500
00:27:58,539 --> 00:28:01,041
I met with Hwal-sung,
and he didn't know anything.

501
00:28:01,125 --> 00:28:04,378
But this punk is always lying,
so I find him hard to believe.

502
00:28:04,461 --> 00:28:06,213
<i>That's not the problem.</i>

503
00:28:06,547 --> 00:28:08,382
<i>- I think Da-rae got kidnapped.</i>
- What?

504
00:28:09,383 --> 00:28:10,593
It's Da-rae!

505
00:28:11,135 --> 00:28:13,554
I think Da-rae got kidnapped!

506
00:28:14,180 --> 00:28:15,222
What?

507
00:28:15,306 --> 00:28:16,432
What happened to Da-rae?

508
00:28:16,724 --> 00:28:18,767
<i>I'm going to the police station now</i>

509
00:28:19,018 --> 00:28:20,936
so come quickly, okay?

510
00:28:47,796 --> 00:28:48,797
Da-rae.

511
00:28:50,674 --> 00:28:51,675
Good job.

512
00:28:55,721 --> 00:28:57,014
YONGBUK POLICE STATION

513
00:28:57,097 --> 00:28:58,432
What's going on, Seon?

514
00:28:58,515 --> 00:28:59,516
Su-jong.

515
00:29:00,017 --> 00:29:02,019
I reported it, and I'm waiting.

516
00:29:02,519 --> 00:29:04,313
What if something happens to her?

517
00:29:05,147 --> 00:29:06,690
Was she really abducted?

518
00:29:07,066 --> 00:29:08,067
Well...

519
00:29:08,484 --> 00:29:11,237
She said she was meeting Yi-gyeong
at the memorial house

520
00:29:11,487 --> 00:29:13,239
to tell her everything we had done.

521
00:29:13,822 --> 00:29:15,616
So I went there,
but she wasn't around.

522
00:29:15,699 --> 00:29:17,618
I only found this on the ground.

523
00:29:17,701 --> 00:29:19,703
Why do you think this was there?

524
00:29:21,205 --> 00:29:22,539
But still.

525
00:29:22,623 --> 00:29:24,250
Yi-gyeong wouldn't do that.

526
00:29:24,333 --> 00:29:26,585
She must've found out
everything we had done!

527
00:29:27,294 --> 00:29:28,712
How did she find out?

528
00:29:29,171 --> 00:29:30,631
Da-rae must've told her.

529
00:29:31,257 --> 00:29:32,883
Do you know what she said to me?

530
00:29:33,968 --> 00:29:35,386
She's disappointed in me.

531
00:29:36,679 --> 00:29:38,681
Da-rae knows everything, Su-jong.

532
00:29:40,891 --> 00:29:43,269
You should've seen her face.

533
00:29:47,564 --> 00:29:49,108
All right. I'll look for her.

534
00:29:49,191 --> 00:29:50,776
How are you going to find her?

535
00:29:50,859 --> 00:29:52,861
But I can't sit here and wait.

536
00:29:59,660 --> 00:30:00,869
YI-GYEONG

537
00:30:00,953 --> 00:30:01,954
JEON YI-GYEONG

538
00:30:02,037 --> 00:30:03,372
YOU KNOW WHERE THIS IS, DON'T YOU?

539
00:30:05,082 --> 00:30:06,500
<i>You know where this is, don't you?</i>

540
00:30:06,583 --> 00:30:08,210
<i>If you want to save her,</i>
<i>come quickly.</i>

541
00:30:40,909 --> 00:30:41,994
<i>- Coffee grounds.</i>
<i>- What?</i>

542
00:30:42,786 --> 00:30:44,788
We found coffee grounds
on her clothes.

543
00:30:44,872 --> 00:30:46,832
Yes, that makes sense.

544
00:30:46,915 --> 00:30:50,461
Does that mean
the café owner is the kidnapper?

545
00:31:15,611 --> 00:31:16,695
Do you have something to say?

546
00:31:19,156 --> 00:31:20,157
Untie her.

547
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:21,241
What?

548
00:31:36,965 --> 00:31:41,970
(If you let me go now,
I'll pretend this never happened.)

549
00:31:42,763 --> 00:31:44,598
Are you trying
to make a deal with me?

550
00:31:45,516 --> 00:31:50,938
(My dad kidnapped you
and you kidnapped me.)

551
00:31:51,647 --> 00:31:53,857
(Isn't that the same?)

552
00:31:55,401 --> 00:31:56,819
You and I are the same?

553
00:31:58,153 --> 00:31:59,738
How can you and I be the same?

554
00:32:00,531 --> 00:32:02,616
Do you know
what infuriates me the most?

555
00:32:02,991 --> 00:32:04,493
The fact that I was in the dark.

556
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,870
While you whispered and schemed

557
00:32:06,954 --> 00:32:09,373
I smiled like an idiot
because I knew nothing.

558
00:32:10,124 --> 00:32:11,625
That drives me nuts.

559
00:32:13,377 --> 00:32:14,711
(I feel the same.)

560
00:32:15,671 --> 00:32:17,423
(I may not feel what you feel,
but I feel it every day.)

561
00:32:22,052 --> 00:32:27,891
(It's as if the world
moves on without me.)

562
00:32:29,059 --> 00:32:30,769
(They have fun without me
and talk without me.)

563
00:32:38,026 --> 00:32:43,574
(I can't hear a thing.)

564
00:32:52,708 --> 00:32:59,715
(But this won't make anything better.
It will only make things worse.)

565
00:33:05,387 --> 00:33:07,222
Things can't get any worse.

566
00:33:09,224 --> 00:33:10,434
I've already hit rock bottom.

567
00:33:12,227 --> 00:33:13,854
I just need your mom and dad

568
00:33:15,314 --> 00:33:16,857
to be as broken as I am.

569
00:33:19,276 --> 00:33:20,486
Tie her back up.

570
00:33:52,392 --> 00:33:53,894
Seon, hang on.

571
00:33:53,977 --> 00:33:54,978
What for?

572
00:33:55,270 --> 00:33:57,356
What will you do, just barge in?

573
00:33:57,981 --> 00:34:00,400
Why not? We must get Da-rae.

574
00:34:00,943 --> 00:34:04,571
If it were that easy,
would they have taken her?

575
00:34:04,821 --> 00:34:06,365
Let's think before going in there.

576
00:34:06,698 --> 00:34:08,033
Think about what?

577
00:34:08,116 --> 00:34:10,160
We must beg or plead. Do something.

578
00:34:10,244 --> 00:34:13,247
What if Yi-gyeong turns us in?

579
00:34:13,497 --> 00:34:15,123
Should we go to prison
and leave Da-rae behind?

580
00:34:16,124 --> 00:34:17,334
Why would she turn me in?

581
00:34:19,962 --> 00:34:21,088
Well...

582
00:34:22,881 --> 00:34:24,716
What is it? Fess up.

583
00:34:25,384 --> 00:34:28,095
I met with Yi-gyeong to discuss
taking over Pyeongbukgwan.

584
00:34:28,512 --> 00:34:31,932
She suspected you and Hwal-sung.

585
00:34:32,516 --> 00:34:33,517
About what?

586
00:34:35,310 --> 00:34:36,395
Kidnapping.

587
00:34:37,688 --> 00:34:39,690
She thinks you and Hwal-sung did it.

588
00:34:41,066 --> 00:34:43,819
What? That was you
and Hwal-sung's doing!

589
00:34:43,902 --> 00:34:45,195
I know that.

590
00:34:45,279 --> 00:34:48,615
I couldn't bring myself
to explain everything in person.

591
00:34:48,699 --> 00:34:50,784
I insisted you had
nothing to do with it.

592
00:34:51,577 --> 00:34:53,495
You should've made it clearer.

593
00:34:53,579 --> 00:34:54,580
Seon.

594
00:34:54,663 --> 00:34:55,789
Hear me out, okay?

595
00:34:57,291 --> 00:34:59,501
We'll say Hwal-sung was behind it

596
00:34:59,585 --> 00:35:02,296
and that we don't know
who the kidnappers are.

597
00:35:02,838 --> 00:35:06,049
Let's say we knew nothing
about the kidnapping.

598
00:35:06,592 --> 00:35:08,010
That's the plan?

599
00:35:08,594 --> 00:35:10,345
Why make things worse?

600
00:35:10,429 --> 00:35:11,888
If I were to admit my involvement now

601
00:35:11,972 --> 00:35:14,266
what good would that do?
It'll only complicate things.

602
00:35:14,725 --> 00:35:17,936
Yi-gyeong trusts you over Hwal-sung.

603
00:35:18,020 --> 00:35:19,021
Let's be honest.

604
00:35:19,104 --> 00:35:20,314
She wouldn't hurt Da-rae, would she?

605
00:35:20,897 --> 00:35:21,898
Would she?

606
00:35:21,982 --> 00:35:23,817
How dare you even say that?

607
00:35:24,359 --> 00:35:25,360
Seon.

608
00:35:25,569 --> 00:35:26,987
Let's only think about Da-rae.

609
00:35:44,421 --> 00:35:45,505
Where's Da-rae?

610
00:35:46,590 --> 00:35:49,509
Don't we have something to talk about
before you see Da-rae?

611
00:35:52,638 --> 00:35:53,889
I apologize.

612
00:35:54,765 --> 00:35:57,309
I helped Hwal-sung
only because he asked me to.

613
00:35:58,101 --> 00:35:59,853
I didn't know who the victim was.

614
00:35:59,936 --> 00:36:02,606
I wouldn't have done anything
if I'd known it was you.

615
00:36:02,689 --> 00:36:04,358
Yi-gyeong, it was really a mistake.

616
00:36:04,441 --> 00:36:06,693
Seon really knew nothing at all.

617
00:36:06,777 --> 00:36:07,903
I swear.

618
00:36:09,237 --> 00:36:11,573
So you and my husband kidnapped me?

619
00:36:19,831 --> 00:36:21,458
<i>You're about to be backstabbed.</i>

620
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:23,627
<i>You could get walked all over.</i>

621
00:36:24,419 --> 00:36:25,837
<i>Prepare yourself to divorce him.</i>

622
00:36:36,264 --> 00:36:38,183
You already know
about the crimes Su-jong committed.

623
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:41,103
Yi-gyeong's kidnapping
and Oh Dong-ki.

624
00:36:42,062 --> 00:36:43,480
My mother-in-law's death.

625
00:36:43,939 --> 00:36:46,149
We must use that to get leverage.

626
00:36:47,484 --> 00:36:48,485
<i>I'll give you a hand.</i>

627
00:36:52,197 --> 00:36:53,699
I didn't expect that from you.

628
00:36:54,574 --> 00:36:56,910
You love your husband
more than I thought.

629
00:36:57,244 --> 00:36:59,746
Why are you taking the blame for him?

630
00:37:00,747 --> 00:37:01,748
Too bad, though.

631
00:37:02,457 --> 00:37:04,584
Your husband sold you out already.

632
00:37:04,668 --> 00:37:07,504
He told me that you
and Hwal-sung kidnapped me.

633
00:37:08,588 --> 00:37:11,216
I thought you two
had an affair at most.

634
00:37:11,842 --> 00:37:14,052
He suddenly said you kidnapped me.

635
00:37:14,136 --> 00:37:15,220
What else did he say?

636
00:37:15,679 --> 00:37:17,347
"She's Da-rae's mother."

637
00:37:17,431 --> 00:37:19,891
"Please forgive her
for Da-rae's sake."

638
00:37:19,975 --> 00:37:21,017
Isn't that right?

639
00:37:28,066 --> 00:37:29,067
Yi-gyeong.

640
00:37:31,027 --> 00:37:33,155
There's a misunderstanding
regarding your mother's death.

641
00:37:33,238 --> 00:37:34,865
- That wasn't us.
- Seon.

642
00:37:36,032 --> 00:37:39,119
Don't you remember what you said
at my mom's funeral?

643
00:37:40,495 --> 00:37:42,581
How can you be so shameless?

644
00:37:43,290 --> 00:37:45,000
Su-jong and Hwal-sung are trash

645
00:37:45,709 --> 00:37:47,335
but I can't stop thinking
about what you said.

646
00:37:48,211 --> 00:37:50,213
You knew everything even then.

647
00:37:50,881 --> 00:37:53,216
You knew everything
and treated me like a fool.

648
00:37:53,967 --> 00:37:57,137
Don't you think that's absurd?

649
00:38:03,185 --> 00:38:05,020
That's enough Truth or Dare for now.

650
00:38:09,733 --> 00:38:11,276
I'm sorry, Yi-gyeong.

651
00:38:11,610 --> 00:38:13,236
It's all my fault.

652
00:38:13,904 --> 00:38:16,656
For Da-rae's sake,
can we please end it here?

653
00:38:17,532 --> 00:38:19,868
Da-rae got into Harvard.

654
00:38:20,494 --> 00:38:22,746
You wanted to support her future.

655
00:38:27,626 --> 00:38:30,545
Let it go just this once, for Da-rae.

656
00:38:30,962 --> 00:38:31,963
I beg you.

657
00:38:37,302 --> 00:38:38,720
My demand is very simple.

658
00:38:40,013 --> 00:38:42,974
Admit to everything you did
and turn yourselves in.

659
00:38:43,433 --> 00:38:44,976
And sign the building over to me.

660
00:38:46,853 --> 00:38:48,688
Then you don't have
to worry about Da-rae.

661
00:38:49,815 --> 00:38:51,691
I'm a better person
than either of you

662
00:38:52,025 --> 00:38:53,026
to take care of Da-rae.

663
00:38:55,403 --> 00:38:57,113
It's over. Just admit it.

664
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:01,201
Yi-gyeong.

665
00:39:01,785 --> 00:39:03,203
I'll do anything you want.

666
00:39:03,286 --> 00:39:05,497
Let's talk about it
without Da-rae involved.

667
00:39:07,457 --> 00:39:08,667
Yi-gyeong.

668
00:39:35,527 --> 00:39:36,611
- Da-rae.
- Da-rae.

669
00:39:37,529 --> 00:39:38,530
Da-rae.

670
00:39:39,531 --> 00:39:40,699
I'll untie her.

671
00:39:49,958 --> 00:39:51,042
Oh, dear.

672
00:39:53,795 --> 00:39:54,880
Da-rae.

673
00:39:55,130 --> 00:39:56,298
Are you hurt?

674
00:39:57,173 --> 00:39:58,425
I'm sorry.

675
00:39:59,551 --> 00:40:00,760
(I'm tired.)

676
00:40:00,844 --> 00:40:01,845
Okay.

677
00:40:02,262 --> 00:40:03,680
I'm sorry, Da-rae.

678
00:40:04,931 --> 00:40:08,268
(You should apologize to her,
not me.)

679
00:40:09,644 --> 00:40:10,812
Okay, I will.

680
00:40:10,896 --> 00:40:12,522
I promise to do that.

681
00:40:12,939 --> 00:40:14,566
Hang in there, okay?

682
00:40:14,983 --> 00:40:16,610
Dad's really sorry.

683
00:40:23,450 --> 00:40:25,577
My name is Kim Seon.

684
00:40:27,787 --> 00:40:29,623
I admit to helping
my husband, Gi Su-jong

685
00:40:30,665 --> 00:40:33,293
by aiding and abetting
Jeon Yi-gyeong's kidnapping

686
00:40:33,376 --> 00:40:36,212
and obstructing
the police investigation.

687
00:40:37,422 --> 00:40:39,758
Also, I confined Oh Dong-ki

688
00:40:41,176 --> 00:40:45,388
and covered up facts
about Jeon Yang-ja's death.

689
00:40:45,805 --> 00:40:47,015
I admit to that, too.

690
00:40:56,399 --> 00:40:57,901
Jeon Yi-gyeong's abduction

691
00:40:57,984 --> 00:41:01,196
was planned and carried out
by Min Hwal-sung and me.

692
00:41:03,031 --> 00:41:06,409
Oh Dong-ki's confinement
was all my doing.

693
00:41:07,035 --> 00:41:10,330
I also fully admit to murdering
Jeon Yi-gyeong's husband

694
00:41:10,956 --> 00:41:13,124
Min Hwal-sung,
and abandoning his body.

695
00:41:15,627 --> 00:41:17,253
What do you think you're doing?

696
00:41:17,671 --> 00:41:18,672
Yi-gyeong.

697
00:41:19,756 --> 00:41:22,801
Let me say one last thing.

698
00:41:23,259 --> 00:41:24,260
Su-jong.

699
00:41:24,344 --> 00:41:25,345
Seon.

700
00:41:25,929 --> 00:41:28,431
This is my fault. I admit that.

701
00:41:29,224 --> 00:41:30,558
I'm sorry for lying.

702
00:41:31,226 --> 00:41:32,435
I stupidly thought

703
00:41:34,145 --> 00:41:36,481
it was best for my family.

704
00:41:37,357 --> 00:41:41,361
So give me one last chance
to make things right.

705
00:41:42,153 --> 00:41:43,154
Yi-gyeong.

706
00:41:43,780 --> 00:41:44,864
I'm so sorry.

707
00:41:45,448 --> 00:41:47,784
I know it's hard to accept,
and it can't be undone.

708
00:41:48,201 --> 00:41:50,829
I'm not asking for your forgiveness.

709
00:41:50,912 --> 00:41:52,914
I'll go to prison.
I'll pay the price.

710
00:41:52,998 --> 00:41:53,999
In return...

711
00:41:54,082 --> 00:41:59,087
In return, I need Da-rae and Seon
to live their lives.

712
00:41:59,587 --> 00:42:03,008
All they got was someone like me

713
00:42:03,633 --> 00:42:05,760
as their husband and dad.

714
00:42:06,219 --> 00:42:07,303
Yi-gyeong.

715
00:42:07,387 --> 00:42:08,596
Give me a chance.

716
00:42:08,847 --> 00:42:11,141
I'm giving you one right now.

717
00:42:12,017 --> 00:42:13,018
Yes, I know.

718
00:42:13,768 --> 00:42:15,311
Your Pyeongbukgwan.

719
00:42:15,854 --> 00:42:18,273
Hwal-sung colluded with Lawyer Yang
to forge the papers.

720
00:42:18,857 --> 00:42:20,692
He made it so you can't do anything.

721
00:42:21,401 --> 00:42:26,322
I bet he already put your mother's
other assets in his name.

722
00:42:27,741 --> 00:42:28,825
So what?

723
00:42:30,452 --> 00:42:33,580
Hwal-sung was the start of all this.

724
00:42:33,830 --> 00:42:36,041
I'll clean it all up.

725
00:42:37,375 --> 00:42:38,501
Tonight

726
00:42:38,960 --> 00:42:41,296
I will kill him and go to prison.

727
00:42:42,047 --> 00:42:43,590
I'll turn myself in to the police

728
00:42:44,466 --> 00:42:45,550
and give a full statement.

729
00:42:46,009 --> 00:42:47,761
I'll give you my shares, too.

730
00:42:48,094 --> 00:42:49,637
Isn't that everything you want?

731
00:42:49,888 --> 00:42:51,556
You even get your revenge.

732
00:42:52,891 --> 00:42:56,895
Just let Seon keep Se-yoon Building.

733
00:42:56,978 --> 00:42:58,021
That's all I ask.

734
00:42:58,104 --> 00:42:59,189
Why are you doing this?

735
00:42:59,272 --> 00:43:00,523
Have you lost your mind?

736
00:43:01,107 --> 00:43:02,525
I must make it right.

737
00:43:02,984 --> 00:43:04,903
Everything ends
if Hwal-sung and I disappear.

738
00:43:06,696 --> 00:43:07,697
Seon.

739
00:43:08,156 --> 00:43:09,991
Do you think this makes sense?

740
00:43:11,493 --> 00:43:13,661
Yi-gyeong, if I kill Hwal-sung

741
00:43:14,829 --> 00:43:16,247
before I go to prison

742
00:43:17,082 --> 00:43:18,917
it will all be over.

743
00:43:40,021 --> 00:43:41,648
I'm outside Gi Su-jong's home.

744
00:43:44,442 --> 00:43:45,652
What do you think?

745
00:43:46,194 --> 00:43:48,321
<i>Not just anyone can take a life.</i>

746
00:43:48,696 --> 00:43:50,198
He's just trying to be smart.

747
00:43:51,282 --> 00:43:52,325
Keep an eye on him

748
00:43:52,408 --> 00:43:53,785
and bring him in
if he pulls anything.

749
00:43:55,036 --> 00:43:56,037
Okay.

750
00:44:01,793 --> 00:44:02,794
THIS HANDSOME MAN CAN COOK, TOO

751
00:44:19,602 --> 00:44:21,354
What were you thinking?

752
00:44:21,813 --> 00:44:23,523
Will you really kill Hwal-sung?

753
00:44:23,773 --> 00:44:25,942
Like in the film <i>Romeo and Juliet</i>

754
00:44:26,025 --> 00:44:27,652
do you remember telling me

755
00:44:27,735 --> 00:44:29,445
it's possible to kill someone
and then revive them?

756
00:44:30,530 --> 00:44:34,450
<i>Actually, Juliet didn't die</i>
<i>after taking the poison.</i>

757
00:44:34,534 --> 00:44:37,120
<i>She had taken a sleep-inducing drug</i>

758
00:44:37,203 --> 00:44:39,622
<i>that temporarily reduces</i>
<i>one's pulse and breathing.</i>

759
00:44:39,706 --> 00:44:41,875
Do you think that makes sense?

760
00:44:41,958 --> 00:44:44,669
It's not that hard to pull off
if you have the drug and tools.

761
00:44:44,752 --> 00:44:45,753
For real?

762
00:44:47,338 --> 00:44:49,465
Listen. This is my plan.

763
00:44:50,466 --> 00:44:54,387
<i>You call Ae-su and get the sedatives</i>
<i>and supplies we need.</i>

764
00:44:54,470 --> 00:44:55,680
<i>I need a favor.</i>

765
00:44:56,055 --> 00:44:57,056
Can we talk?

766
00:45:12,614 --> 00:45:15,366
<i>If you get Hwal-sung</i>
<i>out into the open</i>

767
00:45:15,617 --> 00:45:17,911
<i>I'll knock him out with a taser</i>

768
00:45:17,994 --> 00:45:19,954
<i>and then kidnap him.</i>

769
00:45:20,747 --> 00:45:21,831
Hey, it worked.

770
00:45:22,665 --> 00:45:25,210
<i>I scoped out an abandoned building.</i>

771
00:45:26,836 --> 00:45:30,173
<i>Tell the guy in shades</i>
<i>we'll make it look like a fall</i>

772
00:45:30,882 --> 00:45:32,717
<i>and head to the abandoned building.</i>

773
00:45:34,510 --> 00:45:35,637
<i>Wait.</i>

774
00:45:35,720 --> 00:45:37,847
Why would he fall from a height
in an abandoned building?

775
00:45:37,931 --> 00:45:39,432
I know it seems odd now

776
00:45:39,515 --> 00:45:42,143
but it'll make sense to you
when you get there.

777
00:45:43,645 --> 00:45:46,773
<i>Once we get there,</i>
<i>you inject him with the sedatives</i>

778
00:45:46,856 --> 00:45:49,108
<i>and we pretend to kill him.</i>

779
00:45:49,192 --> 00:45:51,736
<i>Then we call the guy in shades over</i>

780
00:45:51,819 --> 00:45:54,572
<i>ask for help dumping the body,</i>
<i>and stun him as well.</i>

781
00:45:58,159 --> 00:46:00,995
<i>While Hwal-sung is dead,</i>
<i>we put his thumbprint on a contract.</i>

782
00:46:01,329 --> 00:46:03,164
NAME: MIN HWAL-SUNG

783
00:46:05,625 --> 00:46:08,753
<i>And then we revive him.</i>
<i>What do you think?</i>

784
00:46:12,131 --> 00:46:13,216
It's doable

785
00:46:13,299 --> 00:46:14,801
if we revive him within four minutes.

786
00:46:17,053 --> 00:46:18,054
Four minutes?

787
00:46:18,346 --> 00:46:19,347
Five at the most.

788
00:46:19,681 --> 00:46:21,432
But one tiny mistake and it's over.

789
00:46:21,516 --> 00:46:22,725
Can you do this?

790
00:46:24,227 --> 00:46:25,228
I can do this.

791
00:46:29,524 --> 00:46:30,984
<i>Yi-gyeong's pregnant.</i>

792
00:46:31,234 --> 00:46:32,235
What?

793
00:46:34,404 --> 00:46:35,613
You're a dad now.

794
00:46:58,886 --> 00:47:00,513
Sir, how old is your child?

795
00:47:01,681 --> 00:47:03,975
Oh, it hasn't been born yet.

796
00:47:05,310 --> 00:47:08,604
- Do you have newborn items?
- Yes.

797
00:47:08,688 --> 00:47:10,690
These are all for newborns.

798
00:47:10,773 --> 00:47:13,735
And over here,
many people also look for swaddles.

799
00:47:14,152 --> 00:47:15,778
Swaddles?

800
00:47:18,239 --> 00:47:19,240
This is...

801
00:47:24,662 --> 00:47:27,165
I'll give you a pacifier for free.

802
00:47:28,833 --> 00:47:30,335
Congratulations on becoming a dad.

803
00:47:30,418 --> 00:47:31,419
Thank you.

804
00:47:32,712 --> 00:47:34,589
Do you perhaps...

805
00:47:34,672 --> 00:47:36,716
Do you sell anything good
for expectant moms?

806
00:47:37,008 --> 00:47:38,426
I can recommend an iron

807
00:47:38,509 --> 00:47:39,969
- and magnesium supplement.
- Okay.

808
00:47:45,308 --> 00:47:47,769
KIM SEON

809
00:47:48,311 --> 00:47:49,645
Can you give me a moment?

810
00:47:52,690 --> 00:47:53,691
Hello?

811
00:47:53,983 --> 00:47:54,984
<i>Where are you?</i>

812
00:47:55,568 --> 00:47:56,986
<i>Can we meet up?</i>

813
00:47:57,528 --> 00:47:58,738
I don't think so.

814
00:47:59,530 --> 00:48:01,741
You should focus on your family now.

815
00:48:02,742 --> 00:48:04,160
- What?
<i>- Seon.</i>

816
00:48:04,827 --> 00:48:06,037
<i>Don't call me again.</i>

817
00:48:06,746 --> 00:48:07,955
<i>It'll be hard</i>

818
00:48:08,539 --> 00:48:10,750
<i>but what we had must be left</i>
<i>as a fond memory.</i>

819
00:48:12,043 --> 00:48:14,462
Quit talking nonsense
and meet with me.

820
00:48:14,545 --> 00:48:15,755
We have business to conclude.

821
00:48:18,341 --> 00:48:20,134
- This is the last time.
<i>- Yes.</i>

822
00:48:20,385 --> 00:48:21,636
<i>I'll come to you.</i>

823
00:48:22,762 --> 00:48:23,888
MIN HWAL-SUNG

824
00:48:25,014 --> 00:48:26,140
"Fond memories?"

825
00:48:26,224 --> 00:48:27,475
He's being silly.

826
00:48:27,558 --> 00:48:29,102
You never know.

827
00:48:29,185 --> 00:48:30,520
Stop it.

828
00:48:30,603 --> 00:48:32,355
He could actually
be in love with you.

829
00:48:33,356 --> 00:48:34,440
Shut up.

830
00:48:36,109 --> 00:48:37,151
<i>I'm here.</i>

831
00:49:04,554 --> 00:49:06,973
<i>I'll cook a decent amount.</i>

832
00:49:09,976 --> 00:49:10,977
Is that a man or a woman?

833
00:49:14,981 --> 00:49:15,982
Let's get going.

834
00:50:18,336 --> 00:50:19,337
Hwal-sung.

835
00:50:30,515 --> 00:50:31,807
What car is this?

836
00:50:54,872 --> 00:50:56,290
They got Min Hwal-sung.

837
00:51:15,184 --> 00:51:16,227
Will you really do it?

838
00:51:16,477 --> 00:51:17,478
Yes.

839
00:52:10,573 --> 00:52:13,701
EXERCISING RETENTION RIGHTS

840
00:52:18,164 --> 00:52:20,916
EXERCISING RETENTION RIGHTS
DO NOT TRESPASS OR VANDALIZE

841
00:53:07,463 --> 00:53:08,714
Wait, who are you?

842
00:53:10,341 --> 00:53:12,301
Why are you doing this to me?

843
00:53:24,480 --> 00:53:26,315
What are you two up to?

844
00:53:27,525 --> 00:53:28,526
Hwal-sung.

845
00:53:29,151 --> 00:53:30,486
I need you to die today.

846
00:53:33,781 --> 00:53:34,782
What?

847
00:53:36,492 --> 00:53:37,576
What are you talking about?

848
00:53:43,833 --> 00:53:44,834
Hey.

849
00:53:45,376 --> 00:53:47,503
Hey! Are you insane?

850
00:53:47,586 --> 00:53:49,088
Seon, talk him out of it!

851
00:53:49,171 --> 00:53:50,297
No, wait!

852
00:53:50,381 --> 00:53:52,049
Who put you up to this?

853
00:53:52,133 --> 00:53:54,093
- Was it Deputy Nam?
- What a joke.

854
00:53:54,176 --> 00:53:55,469
Was it Hee-ju?

855
00:53:55,553 --> 00:53:56,887
They're putting on a great show.

856
00:53:58,639 --> 00:54:00,057
Keep reporting to me.

857
00:54:14,864 --> 00:54:17,616
Hey, do you know what Deputy Nam
and Hee-ju were up to?

858
00:54:17,992 --> 00:54:21,287
They tried to dupe you
and take over the project.

859
00:54:21,370 --> 00:54:23,289
I stopped them, okay?

860
00:54:24,290 --> 00:54:25,833
Did you see Hee-ju last night?

861
00:54:26,959 --> 00:54:28,419
No, we talked on the phone.

862
00:54:28,961 --> 00:54:31,464
She sent me photos
and recordings of you.

863
00:54:31,547 --> 00:54:34,383
I called her and stopped her
from going too far.

864
00:54:34,925 --> 00:54:36,969
Hey, don't you think

865
00:54:37,052 --> 00:54:39,138
you'd rather have me in charge

866
00:54:39,221 --> 00:54:41,182
than that bastard Nam Sang-ho?

867
00:54:41,265 --> 00:54:42,391
What time did you talk to her?

868
00:54:44,059 --> 00:54:45,269
Around 2 a.m.?

869
00:54:51,233 --> 00:54:52,568
Are we done? Hey.

870
00:54:52,651 --> 00:54:53,861
Untie me.

871
00:54:54,820 --> 00:54:55,821
Hey.

872
00:54:56,280 --> 00:55:00,201
Do you think my death
will solve anything?

873
00:55:01,994 --> 00:55:04,330
If you hadn't kidnapped her

874
00:55:05,748 --> 00:55:08,083
it wouldn't have come to this.

875
00:55:12,004 --> 00:55:13,005
You're right.

876
00:55:15,007 --> 00:55:16,008
Hey.

877
00:55:16,967 --> 00:55:18,385
I thought

878
00:55:18,928 --> 00:55:21,931
it would all get sorted out
if I kept Yi-gyeong for a while.

879
00:55:22,473 --> 00:55:25,226
You know how much I needed the money.

880
00:55:26,018 --> 00:55:27,645
If I had that

881
00:55:28,145 --> 00:55:29,146
then by now

882
00:55:29,897 --> 00:55:32,525
I'd have won Mrs. Jeon over.

883
00:55:33,526 --> 00:55:35,945
I really wanted to make things work
with Yi-gyeong.

884
00:55:36,987 --> 00:55:38,823
That was my last option.

885
00:55:40,866 --> 00:55:41,867
Hwal-sung.

886
00:55:42,827 --> 00:55:43,911
Let's call it quits now.

887
00:55:44,453 --> 00:55:45,579
It's too late.

888
00:55:45,830 --> 00:55:46,956
No, wait.

889
00:55:47,039 --> 00:55:49,124
Hey, wait!

890
00:55:49,208 --> 00:55:50,835
I get it, okay?

891
00:55:52,795 --> 00:55:55,214
Get something from my pants pocket.

892
00:55:56,173 --> 00:55:57,591
Give it to Yi-gyeong for me.

893
00:56:16,151 --> 00:56:19,655
Tell my baby
only good things about me.

894
00:56:21,699 --> 00:56:23,951
Don't you dare tell everything I did.

895
00:56:26,745 --> 00:56:27,830
Seon, let's do it.

896
00:56:36,297 --> 00:56:37,923
I'll see you in hell, friend.

897
00:56:55,524 --> 00:56:56,525
Oh, dear.

898
00:56:57,318 --> 00:56:58,527
They might actually do it.

899
00:57:43,822 --> 00:57:45,908
4 MINUTES

900
00:57:50,079 --> 00:57:51,413
They really killed him.

901
00:57:52,706 --> 00:57:54,416
<i>- He's dead.</i>
- No.

902
00:57:54,708 --> 00:57:55,793
No!

903
00:58:13,310 --> 00:58:14,812
<i>I sent you the photo.</i>

904
00:58:23,320 --> 00:58:24,321
<i>Hello?</i>

905
00:58:26,156 --> 00:58:27,449
<i>He's really dead.</i>

906
00:58:46,385 --> 00:58:47,386
Hey.

907
00:58:47,970 --> 00:58:48,971
Excuse us.

908
00:58:57,813 --> 00:58:58,814
So...

909
00:59:00,691 --> 00:59:01,692
We want to say

910
00:59:02,192 --> 00:59:03,944
he fell to his death

911
00:59:04,486 --> 00:59:07,197
when he came to check out
a property up for auction.

912
00:59:07,281 --> 00:59:09,074
Can you help me carry him over there?

913
00:59:09,158 --> 00:59:10,159
Darn it.

914
00:59:12,995 --> 00:59:14,538
I'm doing all sorts of things now.

915
00:59:26,842 --> 00:59:27,843
What's up?

916
00:59:33,515 --> 00:59:34,600
What are you up to?

917
00:59:39,146 --> 00:59:40,147
Don't come closer.

918
00:59:40,689 --> 00:59:41,732
Or what?

919
00:59:41,815 --> 00:59:42,816
Don't come closer.

920
00:59:43,776 --> 00:59:44,777
What are you even doing?

921
01:00:52,010 --> 01:00:54,930
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

922
01:00:55,013 --> 01:00:56,223
Hey, Gi Su-jong!

923
01:00:56,306 --> 01:00:57,683
<i>Seon, get out of here!</i>

924
01:00:57,766 --> 01:00:59,810
- What about Gi Su-jong?
<i>- What about Mr. Gi?</i>

925
01:00:59,893 --> 01:01:01,436
<i>Are you going to dig with no proof?</i>

926
01:01:01,520 --> 01:01:02,688
Shall we go?

927
01:01:02,771 --> 01:01:04,439
<i>Come to Se-yoon Building right away.</i>

928
01:01:04,523 --> 01:01:07,359
<i>The culprit you're after is here.</i>

929
01:01:07,609 --> 01:01:09,778
<i>Su-jong, what should we do now?</i>

930
01:01:09,862 --> 01:01:11,363
Before Hwal-sung died

931
01:01:11,446 --> 01:01:13,574
<i>did he leave any last words?</i>

932
01:01:13,657 --> 01:01:15,534
Please, please stop it.

933
01:01:15,784 --> 01:01:18,245
<i>Your parents crossed the line first.</i>

934
01:01:18,328 --> 01:01:19,538
<i>Don't come closer.</i>

935
01:01:19,788 --> 01:01:21,623
Stay there! Don't come closer!

936
01:01:25,669 --> 01:01:27,671
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
